definitions.definition: A small village in Burton upon Stather parish, North Lincolnshire district, Lincolnshire , England ; Normanby Hall and Country Park is nearby, and Normanby Park steelworks was to the south ( OS grid ref SE8816 ) .
A village and civil parish (without a council) in Ryedale district, North Yorkshire , England ( OS grid ref SE7381 ) .
A suburban area in Redcar and Cleveland district, North Yorkshire ( OS grid ref NZ5418 ) .
A hamlet in Scarborough district, North Yorkshire ( OS grid ref NZ9206 ) .
A former township in Grey County , Ontario , Canada , now part of West Grey .
large river system in northern Queensland , Australia which flows into the Pacific Ocean ; in full, the Normanby River .
A former shire in south-east Queensland .
A five-way intersection in north-east Brisbane , Queensland ; in full, Normanby Fiveways .
A northern suburb of Dunedin , Otago , South Island , New Zealand .
A small town in Taranaki , North Island , New Zealand
